836|"     Dear Hubert, if I ever found     A wishing-carpet lying round,     I'd stand upon it, and I'd say:     'Take me to Hubert, right away!'     And then we'd travel very far     To where the magic countries are     That you and I will never see,     And choose the loveliest gifts for you, from me."|FALSE
836|"     But oh! alack! and well-a-day!     No wishing-carpets come my way.     I never found a Phoenix yet,     And Psammeads are so hard to get!     So I give you nothing fine--     Only this book your book and mine,     And hers, whose name by yours is set;     Your book, my book, the book of Margaret!"|FALSE
