836|"CHAPTER 2. THE TOPLESS TOWER"|FALSE
836|"The children had seen the Phoenix-egg hatched in the flames in their ownnursery grate, and had heard from it how the carpet on their own nurseryfloor was really the wishing carpet, which would take them anywhere theychose. The carpet had transported them to bed just at the rightmoment, and the Phoenix had gone to roost on the cornice supporting thewindow-curtains of the boys' room."|FALSE
