836|"The Phoenix stopped speaking and fluttered away crossly to thecornice-pole; for Cyril had hit out, as boys do when they are awakenedsuddenly, and the Phoenix was not used to boys, and his feelings, if nothis wings, were hurt."|FALSE
836|"'Sorry,' said Cyril, coming awake all in a minute. 'Do come back! Whatwas it you were saying? Something about bacon and rations?'"|FALSE
