836|"'Yes, indeed,' said Cyril, 'I see it is. Oh, what luck! Wake up, Bobs!There's jolly well something to wake up for today. And it's Saturday,too.'"|FALSE
836|"'I've been reflecting,' said the Phoenix, 'during the silent watchesof the night, and I could not avoid the conclusion that you were quiteinsufficiently astonished at my appearance yesterday. The ancients werealways VERY surprised. Did you, by chance, EXPECT my egg to hatch?'"|FALSE
836|"'Not us,' Cyril said."|FALSE
