836|"'It's like trains,' said Anthea, as they swept over the low-lyingcoast-line and held a steady course above orderly fields and straightroads bordered with poplar trees--'like express trains, only in trainsyou never can see anything because of grown-ups wanting the windowsshut; and then they breathe on them, and it's like ground glass, andnobody can see anything, and then they go to sleep.'"|FALSE
