836|"'But we'll take him out, a ducky darling,' said Anthea. 'We'll takehim somewhere where you can't have whooping-cough. Don't be so silly,Robert. If he DOES talk about it no one'll take any notice. He's alwaystalking about things he's never seen.'"|FALSE
836|"So they dressed the Lamb and themselves in out-of-doors clothes, and theLamb chuckled and coughed, and laughed and coughed again, poor dear, andall the chairs and tables were moved off the carpet by the boys, whileJane nursed the Lamb, and Anthea rushed through the house in one lastwild hunt for the missing Phoenix."|FALSE
