836|"The grassy slope was smooth, but under the trees there were tangledcreepers with bright, strange-shaped flowers, and it was not easy towalk."|FALSE
836|"'We ought to have an explorer's axe,' said Robert. 'I shall ask fatherto give me one for Christmas.'"|FALSE
