836|"And all this time he hadn't whooping-coughed once."|FALSE
836|"The path turned and twisted, and, always threading their way amid atangle of flowers, the children suddenly passed a corner and foundthemselves in a forest clearing, where there were a lot of pointedhuts--the huts, as they knew at once, of SAVAGES."|FALSE
