836|"'No, you don't,' said the cook, in firm, undoubting tones. 'I've alwayswanted to be the Queen, God bless her! and I always thought what a goodone I should make; and now I'm going to. IF it's only in a dream, it'swell worth while. And I don't go back to that nasty underground kitchen,and me blamed for everything; that I don't, not till the dream'sfinished and I wake up with that nasty bell a rang-tanging in myears--so I tell you.'"|FALSE
