836|"'Perhaps it's Mr Blank' (not for worlds would I give the name). 'He's aMasonic High Priest, you know.'"|FALSE
836|"A porter was sent away to look for Mr Asterisk (I cannot give his name),and the children were left there to look on and be looked on by allthe gentlemen at the mahogany desks. Anthea and Jane thought that theylooked kind. The boys thought they stared, and that it was like theircheek."|FALSE
836|"The porter returned with the news that Mr Dot Dash Dot (I dare notreveal his name) was out, but that Mr--"|FALSE
836|"Here a really delightful gentleman appeared. He had a beard and a kindand merry eye, and each one of the four knew at once that this was a manwho had kiddies of his own and could understand what you were talkingabout. Yet it was a difficult thing to explain."|FALSE
