836|"'In the absence of our manager,' the gentleman began, exactly as thoughhe were addressing a valued customer--'in the absence of our manager, Imight perhaps be able--What am I saying?' He turned pale, and passedhis hand across his brow. 'My dears,' he said, 'the weather is unusuallywarm for the time of year, and I don't feel quite myself. Do you know,for a moment I really thought that that remarkable bird of yours hadspoken and said it was the Phoenix, and, what's more, that I'd believedit.'"|FALSE
