836|"'I was coming to that. Our respected Phoenix, the Head of this ancientHouse, has at length done us the honour to come among us. I think I maysay, gentlemen, that we are not insensible to this honour, and that wewelcome with no uncertain voice one whom we have so long desired to seein our midst.'"|FALSE
836|"Several of the younger clerks thought of saying 'Hear, hear,' but theyfeared it might seem disrespectful to the bird."|FALSE
836|"'I will not take up your time,' the speaker went on, 'by recapitulatingthe advantages to be derived from a proper use of our system of fireinsurance. I know, and you know, gentlemen, that our aim has ever beento be worthy of that eminent bird whose name we bear, and who now adornsour mantelpiece with his presence. Three cheers, gentlemen, for thewinged Head of the House!'"|FALSE
