836|"'That I wouldn't,' said the burglar, with whispered fervour, 'so help meBob, I wouldn't.'"|FALSE
836|"'Well, then,' Cyril went on, ignoring this appeal to his brother, 'justtry to believe what we tell you and act accordingly. It can't do you anyHARM, you know,' he went on in hoarse whispered earnestness. 'You can'tbe very much worse off than you are now, you know. But if you'll justtrust to us we'll get you out of this right enough. No one saw us comein. The question is, where would you like to go?'"|FALSE
