836|"And instantly they were. There were the rainbow sands, the tropicglories of leaf and flower, and there, of course, was the cook, crownedwith white flowers, and with all the wrinkles of crossness and tirednessand hard work wiped out of her face."|FALSE
836|"'Why, cook, you're quite pretty!' Anthea said, as soon as she had gother breath after the tumble-rush-whirl of the carpet. The burglar stoodrubbing his eyes in the brilliant tropic sunlight, and gazing wildlyround him on the vivid hues of the tropic land."|FALSE
