836|"In shirt and trousers, and crowned with a scented flowery wreath whichCyril hastily wove as they returned to the court of the queen, theburglar stood before the cook and spoke."|FALSE
836|"'Look 'ere, miss,' he said. 'You an' me being' all forlorn-like, both onus, in this 'ere dream, or whatever you calls it, I'd like to tell youstraight as I likes yer looks.'"|FALSE
