836|"'No, miss. Not me, not even in a dream. I don't say anythink ag'in theyoung chap's looks, but I always swore I'd be married in church, if atall--and, anyway, I don't believe these here savages would know howto keep a registering office, even if I was to show them. No, mister,thanking you kindly, if you can't bring a clergyman into the dream I'lllive and die like what I am.'"|FALSE
