836|"Little Tom on the stage stopped short in what he was saying. A deepbreath was drawn by hundreds of lungs, every eye in the house turned tothe box where the luckless children cringed, and most people hissed, orsaid 'Shish!' or 'Turn them out!'"|FALSE
836|"Then the play went on, and an attendant presently came to the box andspoke wrathfully."|FALSE
836|"'It wasn't us, indeed it wasn't,' said Anthea, earnestly; 'it was thebird.'"|FALSE
836|"The man said well, then, they must keep their bird very quiet.'Disturbing every one like this,' he said."|FALSE
836|"'It won't do it again,' said Robert, glancing imploringly at the goldenbird; 'I'm sure it won't.'"|FALSE
836|"'You have my leave to depart,' said the Phoenix gently."|FALSE
836|"'Well, he is a beauty, and no mistake,' said the attendant, 'only I'dcover him up during the acts. It upsets the performance.'"|FALSE
